# Rule 04 - Enterprise REST API Governance v2
# Part 1 - REST API Strategy

# Purpose

REST APIs expose business capabilities.

REST APIs are contracts.

They do not expose implementation details.

Every API must represent a business resource owned by exactly one bounded context.

Never design APIs from database tables.

Always design APIs from business capabilities.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REST Philosophy

Business Capability

↓

Bounded Context

↓

Aggregate

↓

Application Service

↓

REST API

↓

DTO

↓

Client

REST APIs expose business operations.

They never expose internal architecture.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API First Principles

Every API must be

Business Oriented

Versioned

Documented

Secure

Observable

Tenant Aware

Idempotent where required

Backward Compatible

Every public API is a long-term contract.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API Ownership

Every API has exactly one

Business Owner

Technical Owner

Bounded Context

Aggregate

Microservice

Documentation

Version

Never allow shared API ownership.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

