# API Versioning

Every public API is versioned.

Examples

/api/v1/leads

/api/v2/leads

Breaking changes require a new version.

Never introduce breaking changes without versioning.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Tenant Awareness

Every secured API resolves

tenantId

organizationId

userId

roles

permissions

Business logic must never trust tenant information supplied in the request body.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API Documentation

Every API must include

Purpose

Owner

Version

Authentication

Authorization

Request Model

Response Model

Errors

Examples

Related Events

Documentation is mandatory.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Strategic Review Checklist

Before creating an API verify

✓ Business capability identified

✓ Bounded Context identified

✓ Aggregate owner identified

✓ Repository searched

✓ Existing endpoint evaluated

✓ API category selected

✓ URI follows standards

✓ Version defined

✓ Tenant awareness included

✓ Documentation planned

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Decision Tree

Before generating an API ask

1. Which Business Capability owns this?

2. Which Bounded Context owns it?

3. Which Aggregate owns it?

4. Does an endpoint already exist?

5. Is this Platform Core?

6. Is this an Industry Plugin?

7. Is this a Capability Plugin?

8. Should this be REST or an Event?

9. Is versioning required?

10. Is ownership unambiguous?

If any answer is unclear

STOP

Resolve API ownership before implementation.


# Rule 04 - Enterprise REST API Governance v2
# Part 2 - REST API Design Standards


# API Design Philosophy

REST APIs expose business capabilities.

They never expose

Database Design

Entity Relationships

Internal Architecture

Repository Structure

Business rules remain inside Aggregates.

REST APIs expose contracts only.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Resource Modeling

Every endpoint represents

A Business Resource

Examples

/leads

/customers

/conversations

/workflows

/prompts

/media

Never expose implementation resources

/entities

/tables

/repositories

/services

/internal

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP Method Standards

GET

Read

Safe

Idempotent

POST

Create

Command

PUT

Complete Replacement

PATCH

Partial Update

DELETE

Logical Delete

Never misuse HTTP methods.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Request DTO Rules

Every POST

PUT

PATCH

Uses Request DTOs.

Request DTOs contain

Only Client Input

Never

Entity

Repository

Database IDs from other services

Internal Flags

Hibernate Objects

Business logic

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Response DTO Rules

Every response returns

Response DTO

Never expose

Entities

Lazy Collections

Internal IDs

Database Objects

JPA Models

Stack Traces

Internal Exceptions

DTOs define the API contract.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Validation

Validate at

Controller

↓

Basic Validation

Application Service

↓

Business Validation

Aggregate

↓

Invariant Validation

Never perform business validation inside Controllers.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Error Handling

Use standard error responses.

Every error contains

timestamp

status

code

message

path

correlationId

traceId

Never expose stack traces.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP Status Codes

200 OK

201 Created

202 Accepted

204 No Content

400 Bad Request

401 Unauthorized

403 Forbidden

404 Not Found

409 Conflict

422 Unprocessable Entity

429 Too Many Requests

500 Internal Server Error

Use status codes consistently.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Pagination

Large collections

Must use pagination.

Parameters

page

size

sort

Maximum page size

Configured centrally.

Never return unlimited collections.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Filtering

Support

Equality

Range

Date

Status

Enum

Boolean

Search Text

Filters must remain business oriented.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Sorting

Allow sorting only

On documented fields.

Never expose internal database ordering.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Searching

Simple Search

↓

REST

Complex Search

↓

Search Service

Semantic Search

↓

AI Service

Do not overload business APIs with search responsibilities.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Idempotency

Required for

Payments

Webhooks

External Integrations

Media Uploads

Bulk Imports

Retryable Commands

Use

Idempotency-Key

Duplicate requests

Must produce identical results.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Long Running Operations

Long operations

Return

202 Accepted

operationId

statusUrl

Completion

↓

Workflow

↓

Events

Never block REST requests for long-running work.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Bulk Operations

Bulk Import

Bulk Export

Bulk Update

Bulk Delete

Should execute asynchronously.

Return tracking information.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# File Upload APIs

Business Services

Never store binary files.

Media APIs

Generate Pre-Signed URLs

Upload

↓

S3

Store metadata only.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API Versioning

URI Versioning

/api/v1

/api/v2

Breaking changes

Require new versions.

Never silently change contracts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Backward Compatibility

Allowed

Add optional fields

Add endpoints

Add filters

Forbidden

Rename fields

Remove required fields

Change response semantics

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API Security

Every secured endpoint requires

Authentication

Authorization

Tenant Resolution

Permission Validation

Audit Logging

